The plant where the ever-popular sweetberries grow. Fairly small-sized, these plants have been actually known to grow to larger sizes as house plants, although this practice is rather uncommon. Perhaps due to the fey that usually bother the houses which have the plants potted...

The Sweetberry is a highly prized item for Cordorian children, to others, completely useless.  Commonly stuck on the end of a stick and licked, the sweetberry has a powerfully sweet taste that most adults find overwhelming.  Except in Amia, where they are enjoyed by almost all, sometimes even a little too much, in the case of an ex-assassin who craves them with a passion.

A beautiful, ancient elven tome. For its age, it seems well preserved, despite the horrid conditions it has been stored under. Some old elven magic appears to protect it.

This particular tome is all about the art of healing. Which spells to use under which circumstances, how to create various healing potions, what plants are useful in healing and much much more.

There is also a full chapter about lycanthropy and what precautions to take if someone was bitten.

A beautiful, ancient elven tome. For its age, it seems well preserved, despite the horrid conditions it has been stored under. Some old elven magic appears to protect it.

This particular tome has all the details about the elven pantheon. The traditions surrounding each deity, what time of the day they prefer their prayers, what weapons, creatures and offerings they favor and much more.

It also helps one in calling for some divine aid if needed be.

A beautiful, ancient elven tome. For its age, it seems well preserved, despite the horrid conditions it has been stored under. Some old elven magic appears to protect it.

This particular tome offers vast knowledge of the elements and the elemental planes. Even allowing to temporarily conjure an elemental from each of the more common elemental planes.

A beautiful, ancient elven tome. For its age, it seems well preserved, despite the horrid conditions it has been stored under. Some old elven magic appears to protect it.

This particular tome has the topic of summoning, how to do it, what not to do, what precautions to take as well as a list and description of many creatures that can be summoned. But also a warning which creatures should not be called.

A beautiful, ancient elven tome. For its age, it seems well preserved, despite the horrid conditions it has been stored under. Some old elven magic appears to protect it.

This particular tome is a true treasure, containing vast detail of the local but also the general elven history.

The beautiful gem embedded in the cover can be extracted and used as an ioun of intellect. It easily slips back into the intended socket when no longer needed.

The march of time is inexorable, but the blessings of the Lifegiver enable the children of Corellon to live long and fruitful lives, unmarked by the passage of years. Record and preserve the lessons of history, and draw lessons from that which has unfolded. In the end, the sun always sets ere the next day dawns anew.
